User Guide - GO-CRUDAPI

Starting the Server

A. Set Environment

Set the following environment variables.

If the server fails to read these environment variables, it will exit with the following error: "set environment issue".

B. Execute

Next, navigate to the executable directory, and run gocrudapi.exe For a local instance, the listening port will be 5000 For a docker instance, the listening port will be 5555.

C. Test Connect

To confirm server is running OK, use any browser or REST client to send request. GET/ APIKEY will mean connection to server is fine, as key is server generated. GET/ COURSES or GET/COURSE confirms able to read from database.

Running the Console Client

Navigate to the client executable directory, and run gocrudapi-client.exe if url flag is not specified, it will default to localhost:5000 The response output is written to test.log Different endpoint actions can be specified via config.yml

Configuring Test Cases

Actions such as addCourse, updateCourse can be permutated to formulate different test scenarios. In the screen-shot below:

  • config.yml shows some commented out test scenarios. The active scenario is T004 where the actions are defined in tests/funcs.
  • The bottom updatecourse.req is the json payload for action updateCourse.
  • The right pane shows T004.log which is the saved test.log for the test scenario T004.
